Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
commit_power_intent(25.10)                          commit_power_intent(25.10)

Name
       commit_power_intent - Commits IEEE1801  power intent specifications for
       the  design for use in verification and implementation of the structure
       and behavior of the design in context of a given power  management  ar-
       chitecture

Syntax
       commit_power_intent

       [-help]

       [-clpLog <string>]

       [-eco <string>]

       [-isolation]

       [-keepRows]

       [-level_shifter]

       [-power_domain]

       [-power_switch]

       [-state_retention]

       [-verbose]

       Commits IEEE1801  power intent specifications for the design for use in
       verification  and  implementation  of the structure and behavior of the
       design in context of a given power management architecture. The  method
       supports incremental refinement of power intent specifications required
       for IP-based design flows.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each commit_power_intent parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man commit_power_intent

       -clpLog <string>
              Specifies the CLP log file for CPF only.

       -eco <string>
              Specifies the eco CPF file.

              Note: The -eco option is available only for the CPF flow.

       -isolation
              Specifies the commit isolation.

       -keepRows
              Specifies the pre-existing rows to be retained. By default, rows
              are  recreated  based  on  the power domain information. The new
              rows might not match the original rows.

       -level_shifter
              Specifies the commit level shifter.

       -power_domain
              When specified, the command creates the power domains, makes the
              pg connection and saves the rules

              such as level shifter, isolation and state retention rule.

              Note: The command does not commit the rules

       -power_switch
              Specifies the commit power switch.

       -state_retention
              Specifies the commit state retention.

       -verbose
              Prints the detailed information related to the  commit_power_in-
              tent command.

Related Information
